Rec. 2455 (1890), reprinted in 1 Kintner, supra, at 126.
To the extent this delphic passage, which applies equally to civil and criminal liability under the Act, might be taken to imply that Congress did not intend to reach wholly foreign transactions at all, the authoritative judicial construction of the Act, not to mention the text of Â§ 7, are controlling and to the contrary.
